    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a mechanically sound example of the legendary S54-powered chassis. The 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six delivers linear power through individual throttle bodies, reaching an 8,000 RPM redline with precision. Mated to a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M-differential, the drivetrain provides exceptional engagement. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including a comprehensive VANOS overhaul and rear subframe reinforcement to ensure structural rigidity under high lateral loads. The suspension features a traditional McPherson strut front and multi-link rear setup, maintaining the car's celebrated 50/50 weight distribution. Minor cosmetic wear is present, but the mechanical vitals\u2014including recent valve clearances and rod bearing inspections\u2014confirm this M3 is ready for spirited driving or track-day duty.",
